  <sections xmi:id="_8dE4AFFoEdqaVKCjUUesWA" name="Characterize current situation" guid="_8dE4AFFoEdqaVKCjUUesWA">
    <sectionDescription>Here, you briefly examine the current situation or system to discover what the motivators for change might be. The current&#xD;
business or operational environment and the current response to this are studied and described. Aspects of interest are: &#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Current capabilities and how well they are performed&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Current interfaces&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Current non-functional characteristics, such as physical attributes, environmental tolerance and impact, and&#xD;
        quality attributes.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>Any of these aspects might give rise to concerns about the adequacy of the current solution.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_Ee484FFqEdqaVKCjUUesWA" name="Identify Constraints to be Imposed on the System - Systems Engineering Note" guid="_Ee484FFqEdqaVKCjUUesWA">
    <sectionDescription>In the systems engineering case, the list of potential sources and questions to ask grows longer: &#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Physical - How are the physical characteristics of the system constrained? Are there mass, size, or shape&#xD;
        constraints, for example?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Qualities - Are there reliability or maintainability or other &quot;ility&quot; requirements, for example?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Interfaces - Must the system maintain compatibility with existing interfaces?&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_G20oIFFrEdqaVKCjUUesWA" name="Define Features of the System - Systems Engineering Note" guid="_G20oIFFrEdqaVKCjUUesWA">
    <sectionDescription>In this step, you synthesize a description of the new (or modified) system in terms of: &#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Features or capabilities (as described above) and how well they are to be performed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Important system operational scenarios - these are behavioral descriptions of how the system will respond to&#xD;
        stimuli in its environment, and interact with its actors.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The impact of the system on various stakeholders - interface changes, procedural changes, staff changes (skills,&#xD;
        numbers, training requirements).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_kw0WsFFrEdqaVKCjUUesWA" name="Evaluate Your Results - Systems Engineering Note" guid="_kw0WsFFrEdqaVKCjUUesWA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p class=&quot;systemsengineering&quot;>&#xD;
    Use this step to make a concrete analysis and record of the advantages and disadvantages of the proposal, and the&#xD;
    rationale for the decisions.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
